      "correct_option_id": "1",
      "explanation": "1) $\\dfrac{x}{x-1}-\\dfrac{1}{\\ln x}$: $u=x-1$ 두면 $\\ln(1+u)=u-\\tfrac{u^2}{2}+\\cdots$, $\\dfrac{1}{\\ln(1+u)}=\\dfrac{1}{u}+\\dfrac{1}{2}+\\cdots$. 따라서 $\\dfrac{1+u}{u}-\\dfrac{1}{u}-\\dfrac{1}{2}=\\dfrac{1}{2}$.\n2) $(2-x)^{\\tan(\\pi x/2)}$ at $x=1$: $1^{\\infty}$형. $u=1-x$, $\\ln(2-x)\\approx u$, $\\tan(\\pi/2-\\pi u/2)=\\cot(\\pi u/2)\\approx \\dfrac{2}{\\pi u}$. 따라서 $\\ln(\\cdot)\\to \\dfrac{2}{\\pi}$, 극한 $=e^{2/\\pi}$.\n합: $\\dfrac{1}{2}+e^{2/\\pi}$.",
      "tags": ["For2026","실전모의고사","워밍업","미분학","극한"]
    },
